## 2. Story / User Need

Who is the user?
Anyone who enjoys discovering music and creating playlists based on moods or emotions.

What does the user need?
The user wants an easier and more creative way to organize music without endlessly scrolling through thousands of songs.

What problem are they trying to solve?
Finding music that matches their current mood and planning playlists for different situations.

Why does this matter to them?
Music affects emotions, productivity, relaxation. Studying, workouts, and memories. The right playlist improves every experience. 

## 3. Product Definition

What are you building inside the story?
A playlist planner where users travel through different music worlds instead of browsing ordinary menus. 

What will the app help the user do?
•	Explore music moods
•	Discover songs
•	Build playlists
•	Organize playlists by emotion or activity
•	Save favorite music worlds

What is the smallest useful version of this app?
•	 Choose a mood world
•	View recommended songs
•	Add songs to a playlist
•	Save the playlist
